The provided solution demonstrates two methods to find the remainder when dividing 987,670 by 128:

1. Long division: This method involves dividing the dividend (987,670) by the divisor (128) step by step, keeping track of the quotient and the remainder at each step. The final remainder is the answer.

2. Using a calculator: By dividing 987,670 by 128 using a calculator, we can find the quotient lies between 7716 and 7717. Multiplying the integer part of the quotient (7716) by the divisor (128) and subtracting the result from the dividend (987,670) yields the remainder.
Method 1: Long Division

Step 1: Set up the long division:
$$
\begin{array}{c|c@{\hspace{0pt}}c@{\hspace{0pt}}c@{\hspace{0pt}}c@{\hspace{0pt}}c@{\hspace{0pt}}c@{\hspace{0pt}}c@{\hspace{0pt}}c}
